1. On July 10, 2025, IDEXX Laboratories, Inc. elected Joseph L. (Jay) Hooley as an independent director, increasing the Board size from nine to ten members.
2.  Mr. Hooley's compensation will match that of other non-employee directors, as detailed in the company's March 28, 2025 proxy statement, with adjustments for his July 10th start date.
3.  Stock grants to Mr. Hooley will be made on September 1, 2025, prorated to reflect his service from July 10, 2025, until the 2026 annual stockholder meeting.
1. Labcorp Holdings Inc. declared a $0.72 per share cash dividend on July 10, 2025, payable September 11, 2025, to stockholders of record as of August 28, 2025.
2. Labcorp supported 75% of new drugs and therapeutic products approved by the FDA in 2024 and performed over 700 million patient tests annually.
3. No specific future impacts or risks were mentioned in the provided excerpt.

1. Delta Air Lines reported record June quarter revenue of $15.5 billion (approximately 1 percent higher than the June quarter of 2024), but adjusted total unit revenue was down 3 percent year-over-year.

2.  Delta forecasts September quarter earnings per share of $1.25 to $1.75 with an operating margin of 9 to 11 percent and full-year 2025 earnings per share of $5.25 to $6.25, and free cash flow of $3 to $4 billion.
3. Delta announced a 25 percent increase to its dividend payment beginning in the September quarter (July 10, 2025).
1. Tesla's Board of Directors set July 31, 2025, as the deadline for shareholder proposals to be included in the proxy statement for the 2025 Annual Meeting, scheduled for November 6, 2025.

2.  Shareholders who wish to nominate directors for the 2025 Annual Meeting without including their nominations in Tesla's proxy materials must provide notice between July 9, 2025, and August 8, 2025.
3.  Tesla may omit any shareholder proposal from its proxy materials that does not comply with SEC rules.
1. Dollar Tree, Inc. announced a new $2.5 billion share repurchase authorization on July 9th, 2025, replacing a prior authorization with $0.45 billion remaining.
2.  The company repurchased the remaining $0.45 billion of shares under the previous authorization before the new one was implemented.
3. The new share repurchase program has no expiration date.
1. United Airlines Holdings, Inc. redeemed $1.52 billion in senior secured notes due 2027 on July 7, 2025, using cash on hand, resulting in unencumbered MileagePlus assets.
2.  As of the end of the second quarter of 2025, United Airlines’ adjusted total debt declined to $32.5 billion from a peak of $45.3 billion in the second quarter of 2021.
3.  United Airlines is targeting a long-term net leverage of less than 2.0x, and the note redemption is part of their deleveraging plan.
1. EOG Resources Inc. paid $24 million in net cash during the second quarter of 2025 for the settlement of financial commodity derivative contracts.

2.  During the second quarter of 2025, the average NYMEX West Texas Intermediate crude oil price was $63.71 per barrel, and the average NYMEX natural gas price at Henry Hub was $3.44 per million British thermal units.

3. EOG's future financial results are subject to numerous risks, including commodity price volatility, success of reserve acquisition and development efforts, and the impact of government regulations and climate change initiatives.
